    "However, merging models trained from different bases requires neuron alignment (Tatro et al., 2020; Entezari et al., 2022), and several methods address this (Ainsworth et al., 2023; Peña et al., 2023; Rinaldi et al., 2025).",
    "Here, however, we restrict our focus to fine-tuned LLM checkpoints derived from a common base and therefore do not consider neuron alignment.",
    "Weight Interpolation Based Methods.",
    "Wortsman et al. (2022) introduce Model Soup, which averages or greedily aggregates aligned models.",
    "For fine-tuned variants of a shared base, Ilharco et al. (2023) propose Task Arithmetic (TA), a main method in our study (detailed in Section 3.1)."
